    <!-- About us page -->
    <system:String x:Key="AboutUsWindow.AboutUs">Who are we?</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="AboutUsWindow.InformationBehindTheDevelopersOfThisApplication">We are five students at HBO-ICT who are studying to be Software Engineers at Windesheim. For the class SDL we had to choose a project out a few clients. The preference of the team went to this project, The ArtGenerator. Our Client, Jan Coenen is an artist by profession. He was looking for an application that would use the users preferences to make the perfect painting.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="AboutUsWindow.ArtGeneratorTitle">The ArtGenerator</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="AboutUsWindow.InformationAboutTheArtGenerator">The user sees 2 paintings to choose from. By choosing their preference a few times the Algorithm will start to use the preferences given by the user. The application also has a Configuration menu where standard values can be changes, so the user has more control over what sort of paintings come out of the algorithm. The first few paintings are randomly generated so the Algorithm can learn the users preference. This is called the learning phase, where the algorithm gathers data on the user and calculates a painting that generates something that comes close to the users preferences.</system:String>
    
